list.abstract: separate（英 [ˈseprət , ˈsepəreɪt]，美 [ˈseprət , ˈsepəreɪt]），英语单词，作形容词用，为分离的；独立的；不同的。作动词用，为使分离；分开；分成部分。作名词用，为自成一体的物件；独立音响设备；土壤划分。短语搭配有separate from（分离；分隔开；分开），例句为“The book contains twelve separate stories.（这本书包含十二个独立的故事。）” separate及物动词类近义词有split、divorce，不及物动词类近义词有come between、to break，形容词类近义词有alone、independent、divided等，名词类近义词有partition、fall-away。separate的名词形式为separatist。
《separate》是日本著名漫画家驾笼真太郎的最新作品，国内版权由易动漫独家代理。驾笼真太郎，日本男漫画家。他的主要创作方向是面向成人的漫画作品，于1988年在COMICBOX出道。从2002年开始积极地参加了众多活动，向世人展示了自己“不道德的排泄物”。相对中国读者说的一句话是：我希望全世界都能读到我的漫画。请尽情欣赏。

yingyinNormal.en: I know a lot of students here at Oxford have your own separate bedrooms, but when I was a freshman at Williams College, I was not so fortunate.

yingyinNormal.en: There are separate showers for both sexes.

yingyinNormal.en: Rach, do you, are you gonna separate those?
yingyinNormal.zh: 瑞秋，你不打算分开洗吗？

yingyinNormal.en: You're at that age when you want to separate. Yeah, I separate from you, not the other way around.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你到了想独立自主的年纪。是我从你那独立出来，而不是反过来。

yingyinNormal.en: But we have to separate that out. It can't affect our plan.

yingyinNormal.en: And on a totally separate subject, that is a lovely pantsuit.

yingyinNormal.en: I run the hydrazine around an iridium catalyst. It will separate into N2 and H2.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我将肼用铱催化，它会分解为氮气和氢气。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, come on. Your Honor, if Mr. Schmidt's clients wish to bring a separate suit...
yingyinNormal.zh: 得了吧，法官阁下，如果施密特先生的当事人想另行起诉...

yingyinNormal.en: When the IRS questions us in separate rooms, we need to have our stories straight.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当我们被关在不同房间被国税局审问时，我们的答案必须一致啊。

yingyinNormal.en: It's not a simple pass-fail. It's an evaluation tool we use to separate applicants.
yingyinNormal.zh: 考试不是通过没通过这么简单，而是我们区分申请者的评估手段。

yingyinNormal.en: Access the elevator with fingerprint recognition and open 3 separate combination locks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 进入搭载装有指纹识别系统的电梯，然后分别打开三个组合密码锁。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine, I'll tell you. A lichen is an organism made up of two separate species, fungi and algae.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还是跟你们分享一下吧，地衣是由菌类和藻类这两不同的物种组成的复合有机体。

yingyinNormal.en: No, I'm getting three separate heartbeats. Three? You guys were worried I wouldn't even have one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是，我听到三个心跳音。三个？你们还担心我怀不成。

yingyinNormal.en: I, personally, will see to it that your organs are removed and placed in separate jewel-encrusted jars. Thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我，将亲自监督你的内脏被移除并分别放入镶满宝石的罐子里。谢谢。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, guys, tell you what. Let's split the class into two separate businesses and see how you do for yourselves.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，同学们，接下来，咱们把全班分成两个独立的公司来看看你们会为自己做些什么。

yingyinNormal.en: Another piece of advice, is that couples use separate blankets if one of the partners is a particularly restless sleeper.
yingyinNormal.zh: 另一个建议，如果情侣中有人较晚睡，可以用不同的被子。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't understand. Yes, we shared a uterus for nine months, but since then we've pretty much gone our own separate ways.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不明白，不错，我们共同在一个子宫里待过九个月，但此后我们就你走阳关道，我走独木桥了。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, both selective mutism and an inability to separate from one's mother can stem from a pathological fear of women.
yingyinNormal.zh: 无论是选择性缄默症还是无法离开母亲独自生活，都可能是源于对女性的病理性恐惧。

yingyinNormal.en: On my 12th birthday, I really wanted a titanium centrifuge, so, you know, I could separate radioactive isotopes. Of course.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我12岁生日的时候，我非常想要一个钛离心分离机，这样，我就可以分离放射性同位素了。当然。

yingyinNormal.en: And when the two worlds are separate, everything is fine. When you have romantic love and work for hire, everything is fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这两个世界分开时，所有事情都井井有条，你同时拥有爱情和工作时，两者并不冲突。

word_usage.usage:
表示“分开”时：
separate指将混合物按不同类别分开，也指把紧连在一起或溶合在一起的东西分开：She separated the whites and yolks of 4 eggs. 她把4个鸡蛋的蛋清和蛋黄分开。
divide指把两个区域分隔开，或将一个整体分为若干部分，有时含平均划分之意：This cake is divided into four equal parts. 这个苹果被分成了4等份。
